          Applying a natural capital approach to Fisheries Management
        </strong>
      </p>
      <p class="govuk-body case-study-description">
        MMO and Defra are developing England's first natural capital-based Fisheries Management Plan for pelagic fisheries in the south-west and Celtic Sea, using mNCEA guidance. A partnership approach with industry, policymakers, regulators, eNGOs and other stakeholders has built collaborative understanding of the wider system that affects and is affected by the state of pelagic fish stocks and their management in the FMP area. The partnership has developed legally binding, time-bound actions to deliver better outcomes for fish stocks, their ecosystem and dependent livelihoods.
      </p>
