          Arts-based approaches to assess Cultural Ecosystem Services in the East Marine Plan area
        </strong>
      </p>
      <p class="govuk-body case-study-description">
        The Cefas Seascapes project explored arts-based approaches to capture Cultural Ecosystem Services from marine and coastal environments. Workshop participants created photomontages reflecting their personal connections to these environments and were interviewed about their artworks. This approach provided a richer understanding of Cultural Ecosystem Services values than traditional survey methods alone, demonstrating how such evidence can complement economic methods to inform more holistic trade-off analysis and decision-making.
      </p>
